ogical operations (erode, \nfill, and dilate) on the binary image to eliminate holes and \nreduce noise (see region in Figure 6 before the skin filter and \n","Fit a diamond to the head (Figure 6, right; see [2]). \n","Using the line that divides the head and the torso, search \nfor shoulder edge pixels below in perpendicular \ndirection. Once a number of edge pixels is found, fit a \nline to each of the shoulder edges using linear regression \n(see lines and diamond in right, Figure 6). \n","\u0083 The user may chose to save only anonymous pictures of his \nactivities. In this case, the system only saves the silhouette \n(e.g., bottom of Figure 6). This is important because his \nfacial expressions may be considered very private (the user \nmay also choose to mask only the faces) \n"],"Page":6,"Number":6,"Type":"Figure","CaptionBB":[93,381,306,412],"Height":1100,"Width":850,"DPI":100,"ImageBB":[85,100,402,379]}